The paper proposes a method for evolving neural network controllers that are robust to variations in environmental conditions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are also relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on a car racing problem, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper involves the evolution of controllers for a swarm robotic problem, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
